{"name": "pure-agent", "metadata": {"name": "pure-agent", "version": "0.1.1", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 3 - Alpha", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8"], "home_page": "https://github.com/yourusername/pbot", "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "A brief description of the package.", "upload_time": 1734922351}, "documentation": ["## Quickstart\n\nFirst install the packages:\n\n```bash\n\npip install pure_agent \n```\n\nsetup your config.yaml\n```yaml\nenv:\n  api_key: xxx\ninfer_params:\n  model: gpt-4o-mini\n  temperature: 0.8\n  top_p: 0.8\n  max_tokens: 512\n```\n\nwrite your first agent based on pure\\_agent!\n```python\nfrom pure_agent import *\n\nclass MyAgent(BaseAgent):\n    @append_msg('msgs')\n    def greeting(self, sys_name, prompt):\n        with RoleCtx('system'):\n            yield f\"You are a helpful assistant, your name is {sys_name}.\"\n        with RoleCtx('user'):\n            yield prompt\n\nsys_names = ['pbot0', 'pbot1']\nprompts = ['who are u?', 'who are u?']\nwith MultiThreadExecutor(10, '.cache') as pool:\n    for i in range(len(sys_names)):\n        agent = MyAgent(client_config='config.yaml')\n        task = agent.greeting(sys_names[i], prompts[i])\n        # print(pretty_print_nested(msgs))\n        pool.submit(task)\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "pure_agent.client", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "pure_agent.client.OpenAIClient", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "pure_agent.client.OpenAIClient.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "config", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pure_agent.client.OpenAIClient._request_openai", "asynchrono